        "content": "<p>Hello! I have a question on how objects get handled in Lean's runtime.<br>\nConsider the following two versions of building a tree:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">inductive</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">nil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">br</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">l</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">set_option</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">trace</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">compiler</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ir</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mk2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">nilp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">nil</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">br</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">br</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">nilp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">nilp</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">nilp</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- @[inline]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mk3p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">nilp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">br</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">br</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">nilp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">nilp</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">nilp</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mk3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mk3p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">nil</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is is correct that trying to use as little memory allocations for <code>nil</code> branches is a good thing, if we expect to modify the tree a lot ?<br>\nIf so, is <code>mk3</code> better then <code>mk2</code>, as <code>nil</code> will only be allocated once, and only its reference counter will change, or will  <code>mk2</code> get optimized in some way so that this is not a concern ?</p>",
